               <head>Ta'rikh-i Muhtasham</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Tārīkh-i Muḥtasham by Muḥammad Muḥtasham Khān ibn Maḥabbat Khān Bahādur Shahbāzjang khalaf al-ṣidq-i Ḥāfiẓ al-Mulk Ḥāfiẓ Raḥmat Khān Bahādur Naṣīrjang</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n85018212 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008116463" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4090-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7383">Muḥammad Muḥtasham Khān ibn Maḥabbat Khān Bahādur Shahbāzjang khalaf al-ṣidq-i Ḥāfiẓ al-Mulk Ḥāfiẓ Raḥmat Khān Bahādur Naṣīrjang</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7383" type="supplied">محمّد محتشم خان ابن محبّت خان بهادر شهباز جنگ خلف الصّدق حافظ الملك حافظ رحمت خان بهادر نصير جنگ</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21988">Tārīkh-i Muḥtasham</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21988">تٲريخ محتشم</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Fragment of a larger history of the navvāb-vazīrs and kings of <name key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n2012057976" type="place">Avadh</name> (<name key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n85018147" type="place">Oudh</name>), completed in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari">1253</date>/<date calendar="#Gregorian">1837</date>
                        </p>
                        <p>Consists largely of an account for the reign of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_265857376" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n85018212" role="subject">Naṣīr al-Dīn Ḥaydar Shāh, King of Oudh</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>The manuscript was written at the request of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7676" role="fmo pat">Colonel William Roberts</persName> (Karnīl Vilyam Rāybarts Ṣāḥib Bahādur). However the source for the original is not mentioned
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                        <p>Fair <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">nastaʿlīq</term>
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Copied from an original =-=-=-=-</note>
                  </msItem>
